---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { useTranslations } from "@/i18n/utils";

const lang = "en";
const t = useTranslations(lang);

const CFP_URL = "https://cfp.cloudnativedays.fr/2026/";
---

<Layout title="Call for Papers (CFP)" description="Submit a talk for Cloud Native Days France 2026." lang={lang}>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 md:px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <header class="text-center">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted-foreground">
        Call for Papers
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-foreground tracking-tight" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">
        Submit a talk
      </h1>
      <a
        href={CFP_URL}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="mt-8 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-primary text-primary-foreground text-base font-semibold px-6 h-12 transition-opacity hover:opacity-90 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
      >
        Submit a talk →
      </a>
    </header>

    <article class="mt-16
      [&>p]:mt-4 [&>p]:text-base md:[&>p]:text-lg [&>p]:leading-relaxed [&>p]:text-muted-foreground
      [&>h3]:mt-12 [&>h3]:mb-4 [&>h3]:text-2xl [&>h3]:font-bold [&>h3]:tracking-tight [&>h3]:text-foreground
      [&>ul]:mt-4 [&>ul]:list-disc [&>ul]:pl-6 [&>ul]:space-y-3 [&>ul]:text-base md:[&>ul]:text-lg [&>ul]:leading-relaxed [&>ul]:text-muted-foreground
      [&>hr]:my-12 [&>hr]:border-border
      [&_strong]:font-semibold [&_strong]:text-foreground
      [&_em]:font-medium [&_em]:text-foreground [&_em]:not-italic">
      <p>
        We are thrilled to open the <strong>CFP</strong> for
        <em>Cloud Native Days France 2026</em>! 🎉
      </p>
      <p>
        Above all, this event is a celebration of the French-speaking
        <em>Cloud Native</em> community — a place to meet, share, learn,
        and inspire one another.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <h3>Audience 🎯</h3>
      <p>
        <em>Cloud Native Days France</em> is built for a
        <strong>broad tech audience</strong>: Developers, Quality Engineers,
        Site Reliability Engineers, Architects, Software Engineers, Cloud
        Engineers, Platform Engineers, Product Managers, Project Managers,
        CTOs, and many more.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most attendees are professionals working across the spectrum — from
        <strong>fast-moving start-ups to established enterprises</strong>,
        and the <strong>innovative SMBs</strong> in between. Your talk will
        land in front of peers facing similar challenges and hungry for new
        solutions.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <h3>Talk formats 🎙️</h3>
      <p>Pick the format that best fits your topic:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Lightning talk (10 min)</strong>: Short and to the point.
          Time is the constraint — keep it concise and impactful.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Experience report &amp; tooling (30 min)</strong>: Ideal
          for production stories, open source project retrospectives, or
          a personal contribution. Q&amp;A included.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Conference talk (45 min)</strong>: Go deep on a complex
          topic, dive into the technical details, possibly with live demos.
          Q&amp;A included.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Whichever format you choose, your enthusiasm will carry the room.</p>

      <hr />

      <h3>Tracks 🚀</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Infrastructure &amp; Operations</strong>: orchestration,
          automation, cost management, observability — scaling, resilience,
          and optimisation of your <em>Cloud</em> infrastructure.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Developer Experience</strong>: how do you make engineering
          teams more autonomous and effective with great tooling and internal
          platforms? Includes <em>Platform Engineering</em> stories.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Networking &amp; Security</strong>: connectivity,
          compliance, data protection, cyber risks and the answers to them
          in the cloud.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>AI &amp; Data</strong>: how AI is transforming our daily
          work and the tooling around our platforms — plus everything about
          processing data in <em>Cloud Native</em> architectures.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Other topics &amp; Crazy Stuff</strong>: an idea off the
          beaten path, a bold experiment? Surprise us!
        </li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h3>Our values ❤️</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Communities first</strong> — kindness and mutual support
          run the show.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Inclusion</strong> and <strong>diversity</strong> are
          non-negotiable: we welcome every voice, regardless of background,
          gender, age, or experience.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ecology</strong> matters: we promote more sustainable
          practices in our field.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Digital sovereignty</strong> is a major focus: open source,
          highlighting French and French-speaking actors 🇫🇷, multi-vendor
          design — anything that gives organisations real independence.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h3>Selection criteria 👇</h3>
      <p>
        Our selection committee — volunteer organisers and representatives
        from French-speaking communities across France and Luxembourg —
        favours proposals that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Share concrete <strong>experience reports</strong> applying
          <em>Cloud Native</em> tech.
        </li>
        <li>
          Highlight <strong>open source</strong> projects driving innovation
          and collaboration.
        </li>
        <li>
          Show strong <strong>innovation</strong> and deep
          <strong>technical expertise</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Support <strong>French-speaking and local</strong> projects,
          showcasing our ecosystem.
        </li>
        <li>
          Bring <strong>fresh material</strong> rarely seen at other
          conferences.
        </li>
        <li>
          Reflect <strong>diversity</strong> of profiles and approaches.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        ⚠️ All talks are delivered <strong>in French</strong> 🇫🇷. Slides in
        English are welcome if that makes preparation easier.
      </p>
      <p>
        Don't wait — share your passion and expertise. We can't wait to read
        your proposals and welcome you for a memorable edition of
        <em>CND France</em>!
      </p>
    </article>

    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <a
        href={CFP_URL}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-primary text-primary-foreground text-base font-semibold px-8 h-14 transition-opacity hover:opacity-90 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
      >
        Submit a talk →
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
